title: Leading car brand sales in Italy 2016 to 2019
summary: This grouped bar chart represents 10 different Responses on X-axis for 4 groups 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Units sold.
Response Fiat had the maximum Units sold among all 4 groups, and it was for 2017. The minimum Units sold was observed in Response Jeep/Dodge for 2016.
Among all the Responses, 2017 had the highest Units sold in Response Fiat and lowest Units sold in Response Jeep/Dodge.
Response Fiat and Jeep/Dodge had the biggest gap of 352927.0 between the highest and lowest Units sold found for 2017.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents 10 different Responses on X-axis for 4 groups 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019. On the Y-axis it shows their corresponding Units sold.
Out of all 4 groups, 2017 had the highest Units sold in Response Fiat and 2016 had the lowest Units sold in Response Jeep/Dodge.
In Response Fiat, 2017 had the highest Units sold among all 10 Responses and it has the lowest Units sold in Response Jeep/Dodge.
Response Fiat and Jeep/Dodge had the biggest gap of 352927.0 between the highest and lowest Units sold found for 2017.
Among the groups, 2017 had the biggest difference in Units sold. Where the maximum Units sold was 8.13 times larger than the minimum Units sold.

In Response Fiat, 2017 had the highest Units sold 402430.0 among the 4 groups and in Jeep/Dodge, 2016 had the lowest Units sold 40456.0. The second highest Units sold 323342.0 was observed for 2017 in Response Fiat.
On average, the Response Fiat had the highest Units sold for all 4 groups 2016, 2017, 2018, and 2019. Whereas Dacia had the lowest average Units sold.
